{"article_id":"0RrEILEcdgO1LRx1","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"165,000 Jobs Added In April ,","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Jobless Rate Fell To 7.5 Percent","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"The nation 's jobless rate edged down to 7.5 percent in April from 7.6 percent in March","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"and employers added 165,000 jobs to their payrolls last month ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"the Bureau of Labor Statistics reported Friday morning .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"The news was better","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"than economists were expecting .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Before the report 's release , economists thought","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"BLS would say","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"that 140,000 to 150,000 jobs were added to payrolls last month","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"and that the jobless rate remained unchanged .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"Deeper into the report , there was also good news about previous months .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"The bureau now says","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"there were an estimated 332,000 jobs","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"added to payrolls in February","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"and 138,000 added in March .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Both figures are substantial increases from previous estimates","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"of 268,000 jobs added in February and just 88,000 in March .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Still , job growth","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"since the economy emerged from recession in mid-2009","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"has been more modest than during other recoveries .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"We 'll have more from the report and reactions to it","depth":4},{"id":23,"text":"as the morning continues .","depth":4},{"id":24,"text":"Figuring how why the stock market goes up or down is always complicated ,","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"but","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"as The Wall Street Journal and others are pointing out ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"the employment report does seem to be the major reason","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"why stock indexes are up sharply .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"The Dow Jones industrial average is in record-high territory","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"and looks like it could close above 15,000 for the first time .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"The S & P 500 might end the day above 1,600 for the first time .","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"Update at 9:55 a.m . ET .","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"`` Some Good News , ''","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"But Obama 's Policies Still Are n't Working ,","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"Boehner Says :","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"`` There 's some good news in today 's report ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"but the president 's policies still are n't providing the robust economic growth and job creation","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"the American people desperately need , ''","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"House Speaker John Boehner , R-Ohio , says in a statement","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"distributed by his office .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"Update at 9:40 a.m . ET .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"White House Calls News Further Evidence Of Recovery :","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"`` While more work remains to be done ,","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"today 's employment report provides further evidence","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"that the U.S. economy is continuing to recover from the worst downturn since the Great Depression , ''","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"the president 's top economic adviser , Alan Krueger , writes on the White House blog .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"Update at 9:22 a.m . ET .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"`` Good News ,","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"But It Should Be Better . ''","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"Echoing a point","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"we made earlier","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"- that the economy has not been creating as many jobs","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"since it emerged from recession in mid-2009","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"as it did","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"following other downturns -","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"economist Hugh Johnson tells our Newscast Desk","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"that Friday 's report is :","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"Update at 9:15 a.m . ET .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Where Was Most Of The Growth ? --","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"`` Professional and business services '' firms added 73,000 jobs ,","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"of which 30,800 were at temporary help providers .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"Update at 9:05 a.m . ET .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"Better Than Expected","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"`` Despite The Sequester '' :","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"`` With an increase of 165,000 jobs in April ,","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"and following the significant upward revisions for February and March ,","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"the job market looks better than expected","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"despite the sequester or issues like the rising cost","depth":15},{"id":69,"text":"of providing health care benefits , ''","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"says Conference Board economist Kathy Bostjancic in a statement","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"sent to reporters .","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"Update at 9 a.m . ET .","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"Recovery 's Demise Is `` Grossly Exaggerated '' :","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"Paraphrasing Mark Twain ,","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"TD Securities global head of research Eric Green tells Bloomberg News","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"that `` the demise of this recovery is grossly exaggerated . ... We 're still in a soft patch ,","depth":15},{"id":77,"text":"but the job market is not falling apart .","depth":15},{"id":78,"text":"The U.S. labor market is in much better shape","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"than most people feared . ''","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"`` The economy has created an average of 208,000 jobs a month from November through April , ''","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"The Associated Press notes ,","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"which is more than the 138,000 average in previous six months .","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"Update at 8:50 a.m . ET .","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"Jobless Rate 's Recent Highs And Lows :","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"At 7.5 percent , the unemployment rate remains at the lowest level","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"it 's been since December 2007 's 7.3 percent .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"That was the month","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"the economy sank into its latest recession","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"( which technically ended in the early summer of 2009 ) .","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"The jobless rate 's recent peak was 10 percent , in October 2009 .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"Unemployment rates often continue to rise","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"even after the economy starts to heal","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"because employers remain wary of adding on workers .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"One defining feature of the economy 's post-2009 recovery has been the continued reluctance of employers","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"to add on large numbers of employees .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"That 's why the jobless rate has come down less , and more slowly , than after some other recessions .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"Update at 8:40 a.m . ET .","depth":6},{"id":98,"text":"February And March Job Growth Estimates Revised Upward :","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"The bureau now says","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"there were an estimated 332,000 jobs added to payrolls in February","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"and 138,000 added in March .","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"Both figures are substantial increases from the bureau 's previous estimates","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"- of 268,000 jobs added in February","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"and just 88,000 in March .","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"Related post from Planet Money :","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"Millions Of Americans Are Leaving The 